<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>It&#39;s a sound I hear all the time in video games and movies nowadays where the low brass plays a tremendous role in both creating and releasing tension. I&#39;m aware that early 20th century composers such as Mahler, Shostakovich, Holst, etc were some of the first to dabble with &quot;cosmic-sized&quot; orchestration, with brass sections getting louder and more dominant. </p> <p>However, I would love to know of some more past and contemporary composers that really play around with Brass/Low Brass, especially that use &quot;Jazz/Modern Harmonies&quot; such as cluster chords, Quartal Harmonies, 7ths+Extended Harmonies, etc. </p> <p>Some pieces that come to mind are:</p> <p>Sun-treader by Carl Ruggles <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VMOyDhxwfM&amp;ab_channel=Precipotato">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VMOyDhxwfM&amp;ab_channel=Precipotato</a></p> <p>Space Chords by the Blue Devils <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2EDIDCdy5Es&amp;ab_channel=ChristensenMedia">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2EDIDCdy5Es&amp;ab_channel=ChristensenMedia</a></p> <p>El Mar Mediterrani by Ryuichi Sakamoto <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8P3796nsYFg&amp;ab_channel=HappySarah">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8P3796nsYFg&amp;ab_channel=HappySarah</a></p> <p>FFVII Soundtrack Live by Nobuo Uematsu (unknown arranger) <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T5OsMJUVXYA&amp;list=LL&amp;index=1&amp;ab_channel=UKRAINEFOREVER">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T5OsMJUVXYA&amp;list=LL&amp;index=1&amp;ab_channel=UKRAINEFOREVER</a></p> <p>SSBM Opening by Kentaro Ishizaka et al <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RXs4-M-ZiOg&amp;ab_channel=SSBMTemple">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RXs4-M-ZiOg&amp;ab_channel=SSBMTemple</a></p> <p>Super open to any resources and recommendations!!</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/yung_paradjanov"> /u/yung_paradjanov </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.